      "Building regulations in Scotland are gradually tightening. While the current minimum U-value for replacement windows is 1.6 W/m²K, future standards may push this lower. Installing triple glazing now effectively future-proofs your property against regulatory changes and could enhance resale value as buyers increasingly prioritise energy efficiency.",
