      "Fifth, assess the product range. Some installers push a single material or brand regardless of your property\'s needs. A professional installer should offer aluminium, uPVC, timber, and steel-look systems, and should be able to explain the pros and cons of each for your specific situation. Our <a href=\"/products\">product range</a> covers every major material and style, ensuring you get the right solution rather than the only solution.",
      "Sixth, scrutinise the survey process. A proper technical survey should take at least 30 minutes for a typical house, involving detailed measurement, assessment of the existing substrate, discussion of ventilation requirements, and identification of any structural issues. Be wary of installers who measure from the street or provide a quote after a five-minute walk-around. Accurate surveying prevents the costly errors that plague rushed installations.",
      "Seventh, evaluate aftercare and warranty terms. The industry standard is a ten-year guarantee on frames and hardware, but the terms vary. Does the warranty cover both parts and labour? Is there a call-out charge for warranty repairs? How responsive is the company to service requests? At Alumise, we offer a comprehensive ten-year guarantee on all installations, with local engineers available for prompt aftercare across Midlothian.",
      "Price should not be the deciding factor. The cheapest quote often reflects corner-cutting in survey accuracy, installation quality, or aftercare. Instead, compare the total value: product quality, installation expertise, compliance assurance, and long-term support. A slightly higher upfront cost usually pays dividends in performance, longevity, and peace of mind.",
      "Finally, trust your instincts. If an installer is evasive about credentials, pressures you to sign immediately, or refuses to put promises in writing, walk away. The best installers are transparent, patient, and proud of their track record. They welcome scrutiny because they have nothing to hide.",
      "Looking for a trusted window installer in Midlothian? <a href=\"/quote\">Request a free survey and quote from Alumise</a>. With our Penicuik manufacturing facility and FENSA-accredited installation team, we deliver quality you can see and accountability you can trust."
